WEBVTT

00:00:07.700 --> 00:00:08.779
Huh?

00:00:08.780 --> 00:00:10.080
You're still awake?

00:00:11.420 --> 00:00:13.090
You said you were watching a movie.

00:00:16.360 --> 00:00:17.960
I guess it's hard
to stop once you start.

00:00:18.810 --> 00:00:19.810
Yeah.

00:00:21.140 --> 00:00:22.140
Okay.

00:00:22.340 --> 00:00:24.520
See you in a bit.

00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:26.760
Yeah.

00:00:27.360 --> 00:00:28.360
Oh, wait.

00:00:29.570 --> 00:00:31.060
I forgot to say...

00:00:35.660 --> 00:00:36.660
Welcome back,

00:00:37.820 --> 00:00:38.840
Saeki.

00:00:45.880 --> 00:00:46.880
I'm back,

00:00:46.881 --> 00:00:47.970
Wataru.

00:01:00.540 --> 00:01:03.030
Even though winter has only just ended,

00:01:04.720 --> 00:01:07.050
feeling this warm spring sunshine

00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:09.790
always makes me think back
to that summer.

00:01:38.420 --> 00:01:39.750
A time so agonizing,

00:01:53.540 --> 00:01:54.790
so suffocating,

00:02:01.530 --> 00:02:03.010
and yet so heartbreakingly beautiful.

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:32.620
But...

00:02:36.400 --> 00:02:38.639
it was also when I first understood
what it means to love someone.

00:02:38.640 --> 00:02:40.390
Three years ago, during that very summer.

00:03:10.760 --> 00:03:12.560
Our story...

00:03:15.900 --> 00:03:17.740
began that summer.

00:04:50.800 --> 00:04:54.600
"The Summer with You"
(Episode 1)

00:04:57.400 --> 00:05:01.400
(Three Years Ago, Summer)

00:05:16.033 --> 00:05:20.033
It was almost like
a scene straight out of a movie.

00:05:21.200 --> 00:05:25.780
I've liked you, senpai,
ever since middle school.

00:05:28.220 --> 00:05:30.520
Man, he's popular.

00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:35.480
I'm sorry.

00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:37.850
But there's already someone I like.

00:05:59.620 --> 00:06:00.620
Hey, Toda.

00:06:00.740 --> 00:06:02.559
You're close with Saeki, right?

00:06:02.560 --> 00:06:04.470
I guess so. A little...

00:06:04.780 --> 00:06:07.320
Well, there's something I wanted to ask.

00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:09.560
Huh?

00:06:10.420 --> 00:06:13.349
An underclassman in my
club confessed to him recently,

00:06:13.350 --> 00:06:14.899
but he rejected her,

00:06:14.900 --> 00:06:16.116
saying he already likes someone.

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:20.799
Apparently, he rejects everyone
with that exact same excuse.

00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:21.800
Is that so?

00:06:22.280 --> 00:06:23.280
And?

00:06:24.580 --> 00:06:26.499
Toda, do you know who it is?

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:28.550
Huh? How should I know?

00:06:28.620 --> 00:06:31.140
Maybe he just says that
because he doesn't want to deal with it?

00:06:32.710 --> 00:06:35.709
But the girls who went to
middle school with him said

00:06:35.710 --> 00:06:38.419
he used to date anyone who asked.

00:06:38.420 --> 00:06:40.340
He had tons of girlfriends back then.

00:06:42.180 --> 00:06:43.180
Oh...

00:06:44.360 --> 00:06:46.540
But now he shuts everyone out.

00:06:47.200 --> 00:06:49.889
That's why I think he
must have someone special.

00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:51.740
But he doesn't have a girlfriend yet.

00:06:53.060 --> 00:06:54.739
So it's an unrequited love?

00:06:54.740 --> 00:06:56.540
No way. Not with his looks.

00:06:56.560 --> 00:06:58.309
Really? You think so?

00:06:58.310 --> 00:06:59.810
Of course.

00:07:00.270 --> 00:07:01.340
That's why...

00:07:01.690 --> 00:07:05.420
the girls are saying it's pretty insincere
if it's just a made-up excuse.

00:07:06.490 --> 00:07:10.050
Hey, don't you ever talk about
romance with Saeki?

00:07:10.120 --> 00:07:11.980
Like giving him advice or something?

00:07:12.450 --> 00:07:13.450
Well...

00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:15.250
Not really.

00:07:16.420 --> 00:07:17.780
Actually, never.

00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:23.859
True. No point asking Toda,
who has zero dating experience.

00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:25.010
What?

00:07:26.280 --> 00:07:27.280
Besides,

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:29.550
you don't know anything about me.

00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:32.800
Have you ever had a girlfriend then?

00:07:37.180 --> 00:07:37.890
No.

00:07:37.891 --> 00:07:38.979
What about confessions?

00:07:38.980 --> 00:07:40.699
Whether giving or receiving...

00:07:40.700 --> 00:07:42.410
- Neither.
- See?

00:07:42.480 --> 00:07:43.820
Shut up.

00:07:46.030 --> 00:07:47.030
Wataru.

00:07:49.240 --> 00:07:51.540
- You're coming today, right?
- Yeah, I'll be there.

00:07:51.820 --> 00:07:53.220
I'll text you later.

00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:54.280
Sure.

00:07:59.960 --> 00:08:03.560
Wow, he really is gorgeous.

00:08:04.880 --> 00:08:07.500
You know, I've always wondered.

00:08:08.340 --> 00:08:12.290
Why are you and Saeki so close?

00:08:12.680 --> 00:08:16.240
You're in different classes,
and you're totally different types.

00:08:16.510 --> 00:08:19.470
Plus, he's handsome and a top student.

00:08:19.480 --> 00:08:20.760
Mind your own business.

00:08:22.800 --> 00:08:23.870
Well...

00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:28.370
We just share the same interests.

00:08:29.280 --> 00:08:30.290
What interests?

00:08:31.300 --> 00:08:32.300
None of your business.

00:08:33.100 --> 00:08:34.150
Stingy!

00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.430
The first time I talked to him

00:08:44.540 --> 00:08:47.310
was exactly a year ago,
right at the start of summer.

00:08:49.780 --> 00:08:52.630
Man, what should I do?

00:08:54.460 --> 00:08:57.010
No, not this one.

00:09:02.220 --> 00:09:06.040
I guess it has to be "The Jet-Black Hawk."

00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:10.560
It's not on any streaming services.

00:09:12.480 --> 00:09:13.750
Maybe I should just buy it...

00:09:14.690 --> 00:09:16.340
Alright, I'll just buy it.

00:09:17.240 --> 00:09:18.130
Oh, sorry.

00:09:18.200 --> 00:09:19.600
I wasn't looking where I was going.

00:09:19.700 --> 00:09:20.700
It's fine.

00:09:21.450 --> 00:09:22.730
I should be the one apologizing.

00:09:22.780 --> 00:09:23.780
Here.

00:09:28.780 --> 00:09:31.760
Uh, we're in the same grade, right?

00:09:33.400 --> 00:09:34.400
I think so...

00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:35.790
I'm Saeki from Class A.

00:09:36.050 --> 00:09:37.800
I'm Toda from Class B.

00:09:38.300 --> 00:09:39.570
Do you like movies?

00:09:39.720 --> 00:09:40.520
That one is great.

00:09:40.521 --> 00:09:41.639
I love it too.

00:09:41.640 --> 00:09:42.640
Huh?

00:09:43.120 --> 00:09:46.429
That keychain...
It's Jet from "The Jet-Black Hawk," right?

00:09:46.430 --> 00:09:48.579
Wait, you know "The Jet-Black Hawk"?

00:09:48.580 --> 00:09:50.580
Yeah, I watched it when it came out.

00:09:50.850 --> 00:09:52.100
No way!

00:09:52.240 --> 00:09:54.069
You're the first person
I've met who's seen it.

00:09:54.070 --> 00:09:56.580
It wasn't very popular
here in Japan.

00:09:56.604 --> 00:09:57.674
Even though it's so good!

00:09:58.110 --> 00:09:58.860
Right?

00:09:58.861 --> 00:10:01.240
By the way, do you like movies too?

00:10:01.990 --> 00:10:02.570
Yeah.

00:10:02.571 --> 00:10:05.240
None of my friends really watch them.

00:10:05.620 --> 00:10:07.179
Oh, what kind of movies do you like?

00:10:07.180 --> 00:10:08.659
Actually, do you go to the theater often?

00:10:08.660 --> 00:10:09.660
Yeah, all the time.

00:10:10.620 --> 00:10:14.980
If you have time,
should we go somewhere else to chat?

00:10:15.260 --> 00:10:16.670
Since we're in a store.

00:10:16.960 --> 00:10:18.190
You're buying that, right?

00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:19.600
Oh, right.

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:21.219
I'll go pay first.

00:10:21.220 --> 00:10:22.220
Okay.

00:10:23.860 --> 00:10:24.860
This is crazy.

00:10:24.880 --> 00:10:26.100
It's like I'm being hit on.

00:10:29.560 --> 00:10:32.910
And that was how I met Saeki Chiharu.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:34.659
By the way,
who's your favorite character?

00:10:34.660 --> 00:10:36.739
For me, it's definitely Jet.

00:10:36.740 --> 00:10:39.039
I know, right? He's a real man's man.

00:10:39.040 --> 00:10:40.260
Exactly.

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:44.840
With our shared love for movies,
we hit it off instantly.

00:10:44.910 --> 00:10:46.116
- That scene was so badass.
- Yeah.

00:10:46.140 --> 00:10:47.259
That's pure manly romance.

00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:50.699
- Right? That's my absolute favorite scene.
- Yeah.

00:10:50.700 --> 00:10:53.660
I think it should have been
way more popular in Japan.

00:10:53.710 --> 00:10:57.209
I don't get why people here
just didn't appreciate it.

00:10:57.210 --> 00:10:58.880
Yeah, totally.

00:10:58.920 --> 00:11:00.309
It really deserved to be a hit.

00:11:00.310 --> 00:11:01.600
I wonder why it wasn't.

00:11:07.890 --> 00:11:09.920
We've been close friends ever since.

00:11:10.540 --> 00:11:12.959
He's handsome, smart,

00:11:12.960 --> 00:11:15.060
and athletic.

00:11:15.540 --> 00:11:16.540
What?

00:11:17.180 --> 00:11:21.179
He seems mature,
but he knows how to have fun too.

00:11:21.180 --> 00:11:23.250
Basically, Saeki is just super popular.

00:11:24.520 --> 00:11:25.650
So, what's your point?

00:11:26.680 --> 00:11:27.680
Nothing.

00:11:27.980 --> 00:11:31.570
It's just, when Asada brought it up,
I found it kind of strange too.

00:11:32.120 --> 00:11:34.119
With all his talent,
why doesn't he join a club?

00:11:34.120 --> 00:11:36.080
He has so much potential.

00:11:36.560 --> 00:11:37.560
What a waste.

00:11:37.900 --> 00:11:40.380
Probably because he wants to
watch movies after school.

00:11:40.840 --> 00:11:42.020
Right, Wataru?

00:11:43.600 --> 00:11:45.460
Well, maybe.

00:11:54.860 --> 00:11:59.270
If a guy that handsome approached you,
anyone would follow him.

00:11:59.310 --> 00:12:00.520
Guchi.

00:12:00.860 --> 00:12:04.139
Are you jealous because Wataru
has been ignoring you lately?

00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:05.140
No way.

00:12:05.560 --> 00:12:07.580
He only met him in high school.

00:12:08.060 --> 00:12:09.060
But I...

00:12:09.210 --> 00:12:13.570
know all his embarrassing secrets, like how
he couldn't even drink soda in middle school.

00:12:14.120 --> 00:12:15.410
That's nothing to brag about.

00:12:16.730 --> 00:12:17.730
But seriously,

00:12:18.170 --> 00:12:20.970
even though everyone thinks it's weird
that you and Saeki are so close,

00:12:21.090 --> 00:12:22.349
he was the one who approached you, right?

00:12:22.350 --> 00:12:25.790
He has so many friends. Why does
he choose to hang out with Wataru?

00:12:26.950 --> 00:12:28.230
How should I know?

00:12:28.710 --> 00:12:32.129
Anyway, I have fun with Saeki,
and I can just be myself.

00:12:32.130 --> 00:12:34.360
There's nothing wrong with that.

00:12:37.310 --> 00:12:38.310
Sorry, sorry!

00:12:38.470 --> 00:12:41.269
Wataru, Teacher Yamada called me in
after school today.

00:12:41.270 --> 00:12:42.560
Can you wait for me for a bit?

00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:45.850
Sure, but did you get in trouble?

00:12:46.290 --> 00:12:48.370
Just some stuff to take care of. Sorry!

00:12:49.050 --> 00:12:52.420
Then you owe me popcorn.

00:12:52.730 --> 00:12:53.730
Deal.

00:12:54.090 --> 00:12:55.090
Thanks.

00:12:56.530 --> 00:12:58.180
Alright, one more game.

00:12:59.080 --> 00:13:01.090
And he has a great personality too.

00:13:01.950 --> 00:13:03.970
Am I just a background character to you?

00:13:18.270 --> 00:13:19.640
I'll be leaving now.

00:13:24.850 --> 00:13:25.850
Saeki-senpai.

00:13:30.050 --> 00:13:31.050
Hmm?

00:13:32.990 --> 00:13:34.330
He's taking forever.

00:13:37.870 --> 00:13:39.510
This is way longer than "a bit."

00:13:42.730 --> 00:13:44.340
What on earth is he doing?

00:13:53.210 --> 00:13:55.810
Is he still in the staff room?

00:14:00.850 --> 00:14:01.850
I'm sorry.

00:14:06.610 --> 00:14:09.730
We don't want you to apologize, senpai.

00:14:12.130 --> 00:14:16.080
We just want to know if it's true
that you already have someone you like.

00:14:22.830 --> 00:14:24.760
I'm really sorry for
barging in to ask this.

00:14:25.730 --> 00:14:29.090
If you really do, I was
planning to give up.

00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:32.330
But I heard you always use that reason
to reject everyone,

00:14:32.370 --> 00:14:33.920
so I couldn't help but wonder.

00:14:36.950 --> 00:14:37.950
Mizuki...

00:14:38.110 --> 00:14:41.089
She's looked up to Saeki
senpai ever since middle school.

00:14:41.090 --> 00:14:43.170
She finally worked up the
courage to confess to you.

00:14:44.230 --> 00:14:47.400
So, could you please
give her an answer?

00:14:51.950 --> 00:14:53.300
There's someone...

00:14:56.310 --> 00:14:58.230
I've had an unrequited
crush on for a long time.

00:15:11.370 --> 00:15:12.370
Then...

00:15:15.370 --> 00:15:16.660
I'm not lying.

00:15:20.610 --> 00:15:22.010
That person goes to our school...

00:15:22.050 --> 00:15:23.120
It's okay, Riko.

00:15:25.090 --> 00:15:26.090
I understand now.

00:15:30.750 --> 00:15:33.870
Thank you for telling me, senpai.

00:15:35.970 --> 00:15:39.020
I'll always be cheering you on.

00:16:10.930 --> 00:16:12.010
Wataru.

00:16:13.010 --> 00:16:14.607
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:16:14.779 --> 00:16:15.813
Seriously.

00:16:18.140 --> 00:16:19.746
Teacher Yamada just wouldn't stop talking.

00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:20.930
I said I was sorry.

00:16:21.430 --> 00:16:23.069
Can we still make the 5:00 show?

00:16:23.070 --> 00:16:24.400
Let's hurry.

00:16:25.570 --> 00:16:28.309
Wataru, you always
want to catch the trailers.

00:16:28.310 --> 00:16:30.170
Because it's a waste if we miss them.

00:16:30.690 --> 00:16:32.910
By the way,
if we want popcorn, we'll have to run.

00:16:34.630 --> 00:16:36.280
Hurry, let's go!

00:16:47.650 --> 00:16:48.650
Ah, we made it.

00:16:48.651 --> 00:16:49.969
Salted or caramel?

00:16:49.970 --> 00:16:51.550
Oh, caramel, please.

00:16:52.463 --> 00:16:53.689
No, wait.
Actually, salted. Salted, salted.

00:16:53.720 --> 00:16:54.879
Which one is it?

00:16:54.880 --> 00:16:56.000
Do you want a half-and-half?

00:16:56.190 --> 00:16:57.290
Oh, let's do that.

00:16:57.410 --> 00:17:00.149
A large popcorn, please.
Half salted and half caramel.

00:17:00.150 --> 00:17:01.549
Sure, just a moment.

00:17:01.550 --> 00:17:02.550
Okay.

00:17:03.770 --> 00:17:05.200
Wow, I can't wait.

00:17:05.610 --> 00:17:07.400
- Glad we made it.
- Yeah.

00:17:07.900 --> 00:17:09.190
Thank you for waiting.

00:17:09.270 --> 00:17:10.440
Thank you.

00:17:10.980 --> 00:17:14.030
Oh, that's pretty big.

00:17:14.070 --> 00:17:14.880
Yeah.

00:17:14.950 --> 00:17:15.950
Let's share.

00:17:18.290 --> 00:17:20.120
Oh, sorry.
You're the one paying.

00:17:20.750 --> 00:17:22.290
Then let's eat it together.

00:17:24.310 --> 00:17:25.830
Yeah, great.

00:17:26.210 --> 00:17:28.000
Let's go.

00:17:28.250 --> 00:17:29.330
- Okay.
- Yeah.

00:17:44.250 --> 00:17:46.749
Hey, can't you show up normally for once?

00:17:46.750 --> 00:17:47.889
- Oh, sorry.
- Sorry.

00:17:47.890 --> 00:17:50.150
I just got rejected.
Give me some space.

00:17:56.390 --> 00:17:57.710
Fair enough.

00:17:57.870 --> 00:18:02.450
But love really is
a painful thing, isn't it?

00:18:02.810 --> 00:18:05.490
- I also go through it every single...
- Do you have someone you like?

00:18:05.810 --> 00:18:06.850
Who is it?

00:18:14.290 --> 00:18:15.880
The person I like is...

00:18:18.090 --> 00:18:19.480
What? I can't hear you.

00:18:28.810 --> 00:18:31.850
How did it end up like this?

00:18:46.870 --> 00:18:48.570
Today's movie was really good too.

00:18:48.580 --> 00:18:50.410
By the way, Wataru, you
laughed way too hard.

00:18:50.450 --> 00:18:51.636
You were shaking the whole row of seats.

00:18:51.660 --> 00:18:54.420
Come on, I couldn't help it.

00:18:54.903 --> 00:18:58.583
I was wondering why you laughed
at such weird times. So that was why.

00:18:58.666 --> 00:18:59.716
You caught me.

00:19:02.070 --> 00:19:04.530
I might want to watch this again.

00:19:04.590 --> 00:19:06.510
Sure, want to watch it again next time?

00:19:06.550 --> 00:19:08.680
Really? Awesome.

00:19:09.370 --> 00:19:11.740
The female lead was indeed very cute.

00:19:11.810 --> 00:19:14.490
That's not the reason
I want to watch it again.

00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:15.640
It's not?

00:19:16.350 --> 00:19:17.350
No...

00:19:18.530 --> 00:19:20.190
Well, maybe a little.

00:19:20.440 --> 00:19:22.580
But don't say it out
loud. It's embarrassing.

00:19:23.870 --> 00:19:26.760
But for her first lead role,
she was amazing.

00:19:27.210 --> 00:19:29.010
The chemistry and timing were great too.

00:19:30.810 --> 00:19:31.810
Oh, speaking of which...

00:19:32.030 --> 00:19:34.390
That confession scene in the middle
was hilarious.

00:19:36.756 --> 00:19:39.566
"Right now, the person in front of me..."

00:19:46.070 --> 00:19:47.920
Hey, don't go quiet all of a sudden.

00:19:48.180 --> 00:19:49.889
Uh, was my impression that bad?

00:19:49.890 --> 00:19:52.320
Sorry, it was just so sudden.

00:19:54.230 --> 00:19:57.550
It's that trope, right? Where the
timing is so bad that nobody believes it.

00:19:57.640 --> 00:20:00.399
Exactly. They consulted so many people...

00:20:00.400 --> 00:20:03.540
and planned it for so long, only
to confess at that exact moment.

00:20:05.570 --> 00:20:06.570
Yeah.

00:20:07.510 --> 00:20:10.670
After having a crush for so long,
they got rejected in a second.

00:20:15.730 --> 00:20:20.730
I've liked you, senpai,
ever since middle school.

00:20:20.790 --> 00:20:24.710
There's someone... I've had an
unrequited crush on for a long time.

00:20:34.890 --> 00:20:35.890
Wataru?

00:20:37.220 --> 00:20:38.280
Saeki, do you...

00:20:38.890 --> 00:20:40.180
have someone you like?

00:20:46.940 --> 00:20:48.460
Why the sudden question?

00:20:48.950 --> 00:20:49.950
No reason.

00:20:50.110 --> 00:20:52.800
I just realized we've
never talked about this before.

00:20:54.750 --> 00:20:55.750
I see.

00:20:57.250 --> 00:20:58.260
Yeah.

00:21:03.230 --> 00:21:05.289
It's not that I really need to know...

00:21:05.290 --> 00:21:08.310
but you're so popular, yet
you don't seem to date anyone.

00:21:08.790 --> 00:21:11.840
So I wondered if you already
had someone you liked.

00:21:14.810 --> 00:21:15.900
Do you want to know?

00:21:16.570 --> 00:21:17.570
Oh, no...

00:21:17.910 --> 00:21:19.326
You don't have to tell
me if you don't want to.

00:21:19.350 --> 00:21:20.450
Don't worry about it.

00:21:22.150 --> 00:21:23.350
I can tell you.

00:21:23.890 --> 00:21:24.910
Huh?

00:21:27.710 --> 00:21:29.270
The person I like is...

00:21:31.590 --> 00:21:32.970
Right now, the person in...

00:21:39.770 --> 00:21:42.330
The timing was so bad just now.
I couldn't hear you at all.

00:21:44.410 --> 00:21:45.550
This is ridiculous.

00:21:46.310 --> 00:21:48.209
It's exactly like the movie.

00:21:48.210 --> 00:21:49.610
I guess it is.

00:21:50.130 --> 00:21:52.329
By the way,
did you time that car horn on purpose?

00:21:52.330 --> 00:21:53.530
How could I have timed that?

00:21:55.010 --> 00:21:56.900
Oh my god.
What a coincidence.

00:21:58.990 --> 00:22:01.370
I guess it's a sign
that I shouldn't say it.

00:22:02.850 --> 00:22:03.850
Maybe.

00:22:04.810 --> 00:22:07.660
Besides, talking to me
won't help much anyway.

00:22:08.230 --> 00:22:09.230
Huh?

00:22:10.410 --> 00:22:13.860
The girls in class also say
I look like I have zero experience in love.

00:22:14.230 --> 00:22:15.630
Well, and that's actually true.

00:22:16.190 --> 00:22:17.250
I see.

00:22:18.110 --> 00:22:21.279
So for a popular guy like you,

00:22:21.280 --> 00:22:23.010
I'm probably of no use at all.

00:22:28.110 --> 00:22:29.390
That's not true.

00:22:30.470 --> 00:22:33.500
Because the only person I
want to talk to is you, Wataru.

00:22:35.500 --> 00:22:36.940
Is that so?

00:22:42.010 --> 00:22:43.030
Yeah...

00:22:49.670 --> 00:22:51.870
Then... I'm listening.

00:23:00.410 --> 00:23:02.070
The person I like is...

00:23:11.670 --> 00:23:13.790
Right now, the person in front of me.

00:24:30.230 --> 00:24:32.740
(Next Episode)
Are you sure about yesterday's request?

00:24:33.970 --> 00:24:36.510
It's fine.
Just think of it as a summer memory.

00:24:37.990 --> 00:24:38.990
Wataru.

00:24:39.620 --> 00:24:40.620
Ah, hey!

00:24:40.660 --> 00:24:44.080
Does a pilgrimage mean
visiting the filming locations?

00:24:44.110 --> 00:24:47.449
What on earth could keep
the great Saeki awake at night?

00:24:47.450 --> 00:24:51.650
Anyone would be confused
if a friend suddenly confessed to them.

00:24:52.230 --> 00:24:53.430
Don't worry.

00:24:54.370 --> 00:24:55.970
If I didn't like it,
I would just say so.